## Definition of done

### Module structure
- [ ] Module responsibility can be stated in one sentence
- [ ] Module file created at the correct path (`src/{name}.rs` or `src/{name}/mod.rs`)
- [ ] Module declared in `src/lib.rs` or `src/main.rs`
- [ ] File is under 750 lines (including comments)

### Public API
- [ ] All public types, traits, and functions are intentional (nothing accidentally public)
- [ ] All public items have doc comments (`///`)
- [ ] `# Examples` sections present for primary public functions
- [ ] `# Errors` section present for all fallible functions
- [ ] `cargo test --doc` passes (doc examples compile and run)

### Error handling
- [ ] No `unwrap()` or `expect()` in non-test code
- [ ] All errors propagated with `?` or explicitly handled
- [ ] Error types implement `std::error::Error`

### Safety
- [ ] No new `unsafe` blocks without a `// SAFETY:` comment explaining invariants
- [ ] No `#[allow(...)]` without a comment explaining why it is acceptable

### Tests
- [ ] At least one happy-path unit test
- [ ] At least one error-case unit test
- [ ] Property-based tests added for complex or security-critical logic

### Code quality
- [ ] `cargo fmt --check` passes
- [ ] `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` passes (zero warnings)
- [ ] `cargo test` passes (all tests green)
- [ ] `cargo doc --no-deps` builds without warnings

### Documentation
- [ ] `CHANGELOG.md` updated if this adds a user-facing feature

